The international community is urged to support Lebanon after the assassination of Rafik Hariri.
Calls for a three-day strike and an international investigation were made due to distrust in the Lebanese government.
Saudi Arabia rejected a French-led international probe, emphasizing Lebanon's independence.
Hariri's funeral procession drew massive crowds, with accusations against Syria and the Lebanese government for his death.
The bombing marked a turning point in Lebanon-Syria relations, with growing demands for Syrian withdrawal.
Hariri's legacy as a peacemaker and redeveloper of Beirut was honored by mourners, reflecting a nation in mourning and seeking justice.
